      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hydration is key, and drinking plenty of water can help alleviate some of the symptoms. I recommend increasing your water intake, but not just to \"flush it out.\" Aim for at least 8-10 glasses of water a day, and consider adding some electrolyte-rich beverages like coconut water or sports drinks to help stabilize your electrolyte levels. As for the dizziness and fuzzy head, it's likely due to the lithium's effects on your balance and cognitive function, so just stick to your regular routine and see how your body adjusts.",
